Hi everyone,

I’ve been encountering an issue with my Vivid Hosting 109 radio, and I’m hoping someone here can help me troubleshoot.

Here’s what I’ve done so far:

  1. I powered the radio and connected it to my computer via the DS port.
  2. I accessed the radio setup page using http://radio.local as instructed in the documentation and completed the configuration.
  3. Initially, everything worked fine for a while. I could see the radio in my Wi-Fi settings and connect to it without any problems.
  4. However, I started noticing intermittent connection issues during testing—short connection drops in the Driver Station. (up to 1 seconds)
  5. Eventually, I lost the ability to connect to the robot entirely.

Now, when I power on the radio:

  • The radio no longer shows up in my Wi-Fi network list.
  • I can’t access it via Ethernet (directly plugged in) or through http://radio.local.
  • Previously, it would appear on my computer about 20–30 seconds after powering up, but now there’s nothing.

Has anyone experienced a similar issue or know how I can regain access to the radio? Any advice would be greatly appreciated!

Thanks in advance!
